'''Douglas dos Santos Justino de Melo''' ({{Langx|ru|Дуглас До Сантос Жустино Де Мело}};<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Official Russian government law portal|url=http://publication.pravo.gov.ru/document/0001202410210004|title=Указ Президента Российской Федерации от 21.10.2024 № 900|trans-title=Russian Federation president decree No. 900 from 21 October 2024|language=ru}}</ref> born 22 March 1994), known as '''Douglas Santos''' or simply '''Douglas''' (Brazilian Portuguese: [[Help:IPA/Portuguese|[ˈdowglɐs ˈsɐ̃tʊs]]]), is a Brazilian<!--DO NOT CHANGE TO "RUSSIAN". THIS WILL BECOME AMBIGUOUS ONCE HE PLAYS FOR RUSSIA.--> professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] for [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

==Club career==

===Náutico===
On 15 February 2012, Douglas Santos made his first team debut, in a 2–0 home win over [[Central Sport Club|Central]].<ref>[http://www.girodosesportes.com.br/index.php?pagina=esportes&id=44&noti=19326 PE 2012: Náutico 2x0 Central -> Patativa mais uma vez não se deu bem nos Aflitos (PE 2012: Patativa does not get along in Aflitos one more time)]; Giro dos Esportes, 15 February 2012 {{in lang|pt}}</ref> On the 26th, he scored his first professional goal, the second of a 3–1 home win over [[Belo Jardim Futebol Clube|Belo Jardim]].<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/pe/futebol/campeonato-pernambucano/noticia/2012/02/nautico-bate-o-belo-jardim-por-3-1-e-reassume-vice-lideranca.html Náutico bate o Belo Jardim por 3 a 1 e reassume vice-liderança (Náutico beats Belo Jardim by 3–1 and regain second place)]; Globo Esporte, 26 February 2012 {{in lang|pt}}</ref>

On 18 July, he made his [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Série A]] debut, in a 3–0 home win over [[Associação Atlética Ponte Preta|Ponte Preta]].<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/jogo/brasileirao2012/18-07-2012/nautico-ponte-preta.html Kieza estreia, marca dois goals e dá vitória ao Náutico sobre a Ponte Preta (Kieza debuts, scores twice and leads Náutico to victory over Ponte Preta)]; Globo Esporte, 18 July 2012 {{in lang|pt}}</ref> On 10 October, he scored his first top flight goal, in a 1–2 away defeat against Ponte Preta.<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/jogo/brasileirao2012/10-10-2012/ponte-preta-nautico.html No embalo da torcida, Ponte bate o Náutico com virada em dois minutos (With crowd's rhythm, Ponte beats Náutico with two-minute comeback)]; Globo Esporte, 10 October 2012 {{in lang|pt}}</ref>

===Granada and Udinese===
On 12 July 2013, Douglas Santos signed a five-year deal with [[La Liga]] side [[Granada CF]], for an undisclosed fee.<ref>[http://www.granadacf.es/index.php?seccion=leer_mas&ref=portada+&id_noticia=1692 Douglas Santos nuevo jugador del Granada CF (Douglas Santos new Granada CF's player)]; Granada's official website, 12 July 2013 {{in lang|es}}</ref> On 2 September, he joined [[Udinese Calcio]] in a season-long loan deal.<ref>[http://www.udinese.it/portal/EN/handle/?hil&page=redazione_approfondimenti&vid=1302&vp=1 Udinese acquires Douglas Dos Santos and leaves Torje, Geijo and Sissoko] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015094506/http://www.udinese.it/portal/EN/handle/?hil&page=redazione_approfondimenti&vid=1302&vp=1 |date=15 October 2013 }}; Udinese's official website, 2 September 2013</ref>

===Atlético Mineiro===
On 12 August 2014, Douglas Santos was loaned to [[Clube Atlético Mineiro|Atlético Mineiro]] for 12 months.<ref>[http://www.atletico.com.br/noticias/?p=27253 Douglas Santos quer aproveitar chance no Galo (Douglas Santos wants to take his chances at ''Galo'')]; Atlético Mineiro's official website, 14 August 2014 {{in lang|pt}}</ref>

On 20 July 2015, ''Galo'' signed Douglas Santos permanently for [[Euro|€]]3 million on a four-year contract.<ref>[http://www.atletico.com.br/galo-renova-com-rafael-carioca-e-douglas-santos Galo renova com Rafael Carioca e Douglas Santos (''Galo'' renews with Rafael Carioca and Douglas Santos)]; Atlético Mineiro's official website, 20 July 2015 {{in lang|pt}}</ref>

===Hamburger SV===
On 31 August 2016, Douglas Santos signed for German club [[Hamburger SV]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hsv.de/news/meldungen/saison-2016-17/august2016/hsv-verpflichtet-douglas-santos/|title=HSV verpflichtet Douglas Santos|trans-title=HSV signs Douglas Santos|language=de|publisher=Hamburger SV|date=31 August 2016|access-date=31 August 2016}}</ref>

===Zenit Saint Petersburg===
On 4 July 2019, Douglas Santos joined [[Russian Premier League]] side [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]], signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]]|url=https://fc-zenit.ru/news/2019-07-04-duglas-santos-prodolzhit-kareru-v-zenite.htm|title=Дуглас Сантос продолжит карьеру в "Зените"|trans-title=Douglas Santos will continue his career at Zenit|date=4 July 2019|language=ru}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.fc-zenit.ru/news/2019-07-04-duglas-santos-menya-i-khalka-obedinyayut-prostota-kharizma-i-lyubov-prinosit-pozitivnye-emotsii-lyud.htm|title=Douglas Santos: "Hulk and I are similar in character with our simplicity, charisma and the positivity we give to people"|publisher=FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|date=4 July 2019|access-date=4 July 2019}}</ref> On 3 September 2021, he extended his Zenit contract until the end of the 2025–26 season.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]]|url=https://fc-zenit.ru/news/2021-09-03-zenit-prodlil-kontrakt-s-duglasom-santosom.htm|title="Зенит" продлил контракт с Дугласом Сантосом|date=3 September 2021|language=ru}}</ref> On 25 July 2024, he extended it for the 2026–27 season, with an option for 2027–28.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|url=https://fc-zenit.ru/news/2024-07-25-zenit-prodlil-kontrakt-s-duglasom-santosom.htm|title="Зенит" продлил контракт с Дугласом Сантосом|date=25 July 2024|language=ru}}</ref>

==International career==
===Brazil (2013–2016)===
[[File:Brasil estreia contra a África do Sul no Mané Garrincha — копия (7).jpg|200px|thumb|Douglas Santos with the [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil Olympic team]] in 2016]]

A few months before featuring with the [[Brazil national under-20 football team|U-20's]] winning squad in the [[2013 Toulon Tournament]], Douglas Santos received a call-up for the [[Brazil national football team|full squad]] on 2 April 2013, for a match against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/selecao-brasileira/noticia/2013/04/felipao-convoca-neymar-e-r10-para-partida-diante-da-bolivia-no-sabado.html Felipão convoca Neymar, Alexandre Pato e R10 para jogo contra a Bolívia (Felipão calls Neymar, Alexandre Pato and R10 to match against Bolivia)]; Globo Esporte, 2 April 2013 {{in lang|pt}}</ref> However, he did not leave the bench.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2013/04/06/world/friendlies/bolivia/brazil/1459952/ Bolivia vs. Brazil 0 - 4]; Global Sports Media, 6 April 2013</ref>

On 13 August 2015, Douglas Santos returned to the senior team, for friendlies against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]] and the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]].<ref>[http://selecao.cbf.com.br/noticias/selecao-masculina/lista-convocados A lista de Dunga para jogos de setembro]; CBF's official website, 13 August 2015</ref>

He also represented Brazil at the [[Rio Olympics]] winning the Olympic men's football tournament,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/36666740|title=Rio 2016: Neymar and Douglas Costa in Brazil Olympic squad|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=29 June 2016|access-date=29 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://selecao.cbf.com.br/noticias/selecao-base-masculina/lista-de-convocados-e-enviada-com-duas-alteracoes#.V4f2CBIl_mQ|title=Lista enviada à FIFA com duas alterações|trans-title=List sent to FIFA with two changes|publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation]]|date=14 July 2016|access-date=14 July 2016|language=pt}}</ref> and at the Copa América Centenario in 2016, early on the same summer international window.

===Russia (2025)===
On 3 March 2025, Santos switched his allegiance to [[Russia national football team|Russia]] and received a call-up for the [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly match]] against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rfs.ru/news/221969|title=Дуглас Сантос, Умяров и Кисляк – в расширенном списке сборной России|trans-title=Douglas Santos, Umyarov and Kislyak on the extended list of the Russian national team|language=Russian|publisher=[[Russian Football Union]]|date=3 March 2025}}</ref> despite the fact that three days earlier he had been on the prelist of Brazil for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Columbia national football team|Colombia]] and [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/selecao-masculina/a/cbf-divulga-pre-convocados-para-os-jogos-das-eliminatorias-de-marco|title=CBF divulga pré-convocados para os jogos das Eliminatórias de março|trans-title=CBF announces preliminary squad for March qualifying games|language=pt|publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation]]|date=28 February 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|url=https://en.fc-zenit.ru/news/2025-03-01-duglas-santos-i-luis-enrike-voshli-v-rasshirennyy-sostav-sbornoy-brazilii.htm |title=Luiz Henrique and Douglas Santos called up by Brazil |date=1 March 2025|access-date=3 March 2025}}</ref>

===Return to Brazil (2025–present)===
On 31 August 2025, Santos' request to change sports citizenship from Russian to Brazilian was approved by [[FIFA]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://knowledge.fifa.com/change-of-association-platform|title=FIFA Change of Association Platform|website=knowledge.fifa.com|date=31 August 2025|accessdate=31 August 2025}}</ref> following his call up to the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches [[Chile national football team|Chile]] and [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] in September 2025.<ref>{{cite news |language=pt-br |url=https://www.cbf.com.br/selecao-brasileira/noticias/noticias-selecao-masculina/a/carlo-ancelotti-anuncia-convocados-para-jogos-contra-chile-e-bolivia-pelas-eliminatorias |title=Carlo Ancelotti anuncia convocados para jogos contra Chile e Bolívia, pelas Eliminatórias |trans-title=Carlo Ancelotti announces squad for qualifiers against Chile and Bolivia |date=25 August 2025 |publisher=[[Brazilian Football Confederation|CBF]] |access-date=25 August 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
On 21 October 2024, Santos acquired [[Russian citizenship]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|url=https://en.fc-zenit.ru/news/2024-10-21-duglas-santos-prinyat-v-grazhdanstvo-rossiyskoy-federatsii.htm |title=Douglas Santos gains Russian citizenship |date=21 October 2024|access-date=21 October 2024}}</ref>

